28/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Federal government officials and EU representatives launched a two-day meeting in Belgrade focused on assessing the country's progress towards EU integration. It is part of the Advanced Continuous Dialogue, a new initiative under the EU Stabilisation and Association process.
In other news, Serbian-Montenegrin President Svetozar Marovic stressed Monday (27 October) the importance of war crimes co-operation as a precondition for entry into Euro-Atlantic structures. When asked whether he would extradite former Bosnian Serb military commander Ratko Mladic, he said doing so would be a legal obligation, regardless of his personal beliefs. (BBC, Beta, FoNet - 27/10/03)
